Adjusting Monster Levels
Each monster in this book was created with the help of handcrafted 
tables of numbers and the extensive monster-making rules developed 
for Draw Steel. As such, stat blocks aren't intended to be modified or 
adjusted (with the exception of animals and rivals, as noted above). 
Your best bet for adjusting any given monster is to find another monster 
of the level, organization, and role you're looking for, and reskinning 
that monster while using their statistics.
That said, this section provides formulas you can use to get close to 
the appropriate EV for a monster of a level you want to create if no stat 
block feels suitable for reskinning, or if you want a sense of how Draw 
Steel monsters work.
