Angulotl Tactics
Angulotls are not generally aggressive, and if confronted, a 
patrol of frog folk will usually exchange a few blows before 
performing a harrying retreat to their hidden villages. In 
defense of their homes, however, they become much fiercer 
and more determined. In these battles, angulotls try to force 
fights in or near water to take advantage of their amphibious 
nature and the wet effect.
Simple patrols are usually made up of slippery captains leaping 
into the backline and harassing low-Stamina heroes while their 
minion hordes keep higher-Stamina heroes engaged. In larger 
engagements their tactics become more defensive to protect 
their high-value units. They tend to stay in close and coherent 
groups to take advantage of support abilities.
