*
Siege Engines
Siege engines are powerful weapons that require a team of creatures 
to operate and move. These weapons can scale in size from smaller 
field artillery to massive mechanisms that can destroy buildings.
Adjacent Creature Main Actions
Rather than siege engines taking actions on their own, a creature 
adjacent to the siege engine can use a main action to activate a siege 
engine ability noted as "Main action (Adjacent creature)." In addition 
to their primary attack, some siege engines require an adjacent 
creature main action to reload them once they are used, while others 
have adjacent creature main actions allowing them to be moved or 
allowing a creature to improve the engine's distance and accuracy.
Multiple minions in a squad can activate different aspects of a siege 
engine using adjacent creature main actions.A comet-like projectile sails over a battlefield of infantry squares in front of a cityComing directly at us and taking up nearly half the page from the center-right is a comet-like projectile formed of the orange-edged, glowing blue-purple of agonized souls, whose screaming skull-faces make it appear almost like a crater-filled moon. In the background, at the center-top of the page, is a city of spired buildings forming a rocket-like triangular shape. In front of the city are four rows and several columns, partially obscured by the comet, of infantry squares. Glowing blue-purple soul-projectiles arc towards us, launched from various locations. In the foreground, just aabove the lower-right corner, a projectlle impacts in a huge explosion of blue and purple, surrounded by flaming orange embers and black smoke, The impact throws back soldiers a tenth of its size, easily engulfing a square. In the lower left corner is the smoldering crater of a previous impact, only a few small blue-purple flames and grey-black smoke left behind.

